Vodafone appoints new managing director . Vodafone Group Plc said on Thursday that it has appointed David Channing Williams managing director of Vodafone Limited , the British mobile phone network operator . Channing Williams , 48 , will on January 1 take over from Chris Gent , who the company has previously announced is to succeed Sir Gerald Whent as chief executive of Vodafone Group . He is an executive director of Vodafone and the chairman of the group of companies responsible for value added services , paging and data services . " David Channing Williams brings extensive cellular experience to his new role , and has already made a major contribution to the growth of the group , " said Whent . - - London Newsroom , + 44 171 542 7717 
